= binding isotherm (Binding “curve”)


Protein: $P$
\# binding sites: $N$

- some or all may be identical
- may show cooperativity

Ligand: $A$ : $A_"free" + A_"bound" = A_"total"$

Ligands bound per protein (moles of $A$ bound per mole of $P$):  $overline(v) = A_"bound" / P_"total"$ = number of sites occupied

$overline(v)$ is a function of $[A]_"free"$ not [protein concentration] ($[P]$, $["PA"]$)
Know $[P]_"total"$, can measure $[A]_"bound"$


